{"componentChunkName":"component---src-blog-components-blog-post-template-jsx","path":"/blog/SOLID-principles-in-OOPS/","webpackCompilationHash":"ba0955f1d72b9669930e","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"bfb600ee-37a2-540a-a6c9-96c95a451b66","excerpt":"🚀 SOLID Principles every Developer Should Know 👨‍💻 By Chidume Nnamdi 🚀 S.O.L.I.D: The First 5 Principles of Object Oriented Design 👨‍💻 By Samuel…","html":"<p>🚀 <a href=\"https://blog.bitsrc.io/solid-principles-every-developer-should-know-b3bfa96bb688\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">SOLID Principles every Developer Should Know</a></p>\n<p>👨‍💻 By <a href=\"https://blog.bitsrc.io/@kurtwanger40\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Chidume Nnamdi</a></p>\n<p>🚀 <a href=\"https://scotch.io/bar-talk/s-o-l-i-d-the-first-five-principles-of-object-oriented-design\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">S.O.L.I.D: The First 5 Principles of Object Oriented Design</a></p>\n<p>👨‍💻 By <a href=\"https://scotch.io/@kayandra\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Samuel Oloruntoba</a> || Twitter</p>\n<h2 id=\"principles\"><a href=\"#principles\" aria-label=\"principles permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Principles</h2>\n<h3 id=\"single-responsibility-principle\"><a href=\"#single-responsibility-principle\" aria-label=\"single responsibility principle permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Single-responsibility Principle</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A class should have one and only one reason to change, meaning that a class should have only one job.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3 id=\"open-closed-principle\"><a href=\"#open-closed-principle\" aria-label=\"open closed principle permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Open-closed Principle</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Objects or entities should be open for extension, but closed for modification.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3 id=\"liskov-substitution-principle\"><a href=\"#liskov-substitution-principle\" aria-label=\"liskov substitution principle permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Liskov substitution principle</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Let q(x) be a property provable about objects of x of type T. Then q(y) should be provable for objects y of type S where S is a subtype of T.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3 id=\"interface-segregation-principle\"><a href=\"#interface-segregation-principle\" aria-label=\"interface segregation principle permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Interface segregation principle</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A client should never be forced to implement an interface that it doesn’t use or clients shouldn’t be forced to depend on methods they do not use.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3 id=\"dependency-inversion-principle\"><a href=\"#dependency-inversion-principle\" aria-label=\"dependency inversion principle permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Dependency Inversion principle</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Entities must depend on abstractions not on concretions. It states that the high level module must not depend on the low level module, but they should depend on abstractions.</p>\n</blockquote>","frontmatter":{"title":"S.O.L.I.D The First 5 Principles of Object Oriented Design","date":"September 05, 2019"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/SOLID-principles-in-OOPS/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/a-beginners-guide-to-regular-expressions-regex-in-javascript/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"A Practical Guide to Regular Expressions (RegEx) In JavaScript"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/react-internals/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"React Internals"}}}}}